model

Class Event

  • java.lang.Object
    • model.Event
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Event>

    public class Event
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Event>
    This class represents an Event object that contains a variety of information about a given calendar event. This class uses CalendarView to allow the view to present events to the user, as well as the Day class.

        Constructor for the event object. Note: notes and loc can be null and this should be accounted for
        Parameters:
        day - The day object that is attributed to the event
        label - The title of the event
        sH - The start hour of the event
        sM - The start minute of the event
        eH - The end hour of the event
        eM - The end minute of the event
        notes - The notes or description of the event (may be null)
        loc - The attributed location of the event (may be null)
        color - The color of the event This constructor takes in all the parameters and sets the Event fields to the given parameters.

        public int getDuration()
        Gets the duration of the event in minutes

      • compareTo

        public int compareTo(Event event)
        This method overrides the Comparable method.
        Specified by:
        compareTo in interface java.lang.Comparable<Event>
        Parameters:
        Event - the other event to compare this event to Takes in another Event object to compare the current event to, and compares the two events based on start hours and minutes, returning negative one if the current event is before the other event, and one if the other event is before this event, 0 if they start at the same time.
